window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The stalker is watching, and I'm his obsession.</b></p> <p>Enrolling at Kingston University and joining my mother's sorority was the worst idea ever. Someone's been in my room. They're taunting me, leaving horrific photographs and chilling notes on my mirror.</p> <p>My past has caught up to me, and it's tangled in my present.</p> <p>These brutal boys of SIN have me twisted up. I didn't catch on to their cruel tactics until it was too late. Now I'm being threatened and haven't a clue if I can trust any of them.</p> <p>One deranged watcher. One protective brawler. One determined pursuer.</p> <p>Beckham. Wilder. Royal.</p> <p>I want to hate them for the games they've played, but I can't. I'll need their help if we're going to unmask the true villain—the one coming after all of us.</p> <p>Sigma Iota Nu. Where, one by one, our secrets will be unearthed.</p> <p>Beckham <i>is the second book in the Brutal Boys of SIN trilogy, centering around three men and one woman. This series should be listened to after the Brothers of Hawthorne Hall and Bastards of Bainbridge Hall, as they are connected. For mature listeners.</i></p>"; 
